Springbok coach Allister Coetzee has on Tuesday confirmed Warren Whiteley as the new Springbok captain ahead of their series clash next month against France.Trevor Nyakane, Ruan Combrinck, Juan de Jongh and Lionel Mapoe were also named as charge leaders for &#8220;the SA &#8216;A&#8217; team&#8221; by Coetzee in the squad that will face France at the three-test series in June.&#8220;I think we have a brilliant mix of experienced players who have tasted what Test rugby is all about already, and very promising prospects youngsters who will be pushing for higher honours in the not too distant future.&#8220;In my view, there is definitely a lot of value in having players with Test experience playing with these exciting prospects, who along with the Junior Springboks represent the future of South Arica rugby,&#8221; Coetzee said.Apart from the four charge leaders the coaching team has also included a breed of promising players in the group to face the French visitors.The termed &#8216;A&#8217; team side will again be coached by Johan Ackermann who also guided the team during their clash with England Saxons last season.The &#8216;A&#8217; team will face the French Barbarians in 2 matches in Durban and Soweto next month.Forwards (14): Ruan Botha (lock), Cell C Sharks 0, 0 Uzair Cassiem (loose forward), Toyota Cheetahs 1, 0 Chris Cloete (loose forward), Southern Kings 0, 0 Thomas du Toit (prop), Cell C Sharks 0, 2 Andries Ferreira (lock), Emirates Lions 0, 0 Jason Jenkins (lock), Vodacom Bulls 0, 1 Wilco Louw (prop), DHL Stormers 0, 0 Jean-Luc du Preez (loose forward), Cell C Sharks 1, 2 Franco Marais (hooker), Cell C Sharks 0, 0 Ox Nche (prop), Toyota Cheetahs 0, 0 Sikhumbuzo Notshe (loose forward), DHL Stormers 0, 1 Andisa Ntsila (loose forward), Southern Kings 0, 0 Trevor Nyakane (prop), Vodacom Bulls 28, 1 Ramone Samuels (hooker), DHL Stormers 0, 0Backs (12): Ruan Combrinck (wing), Emirates Lions 7, 0 Lionel Cronje (flyhalf), Southern Kings 0, 0 Juan de Jongh (centre), 